  "texts": [
    "What intellectual property may have been stolen or treated with disrespect by the AI's failure to acknowledge?",
    "Has my privacy and security been compromised by prompting this writing by the machine?",
    "These are key questions for a critical AI literacy.Kris Gutierrez speaks of syncretic literacies in which the discursive practices of students from nondominant communities are positioned in dialogue with academic literacies (Gutierrez 2014).",
    "She calls this meeting point a \"collective third space, a particular kind of zone of proximal development,... an interactionally constituted, artifact-rich environment (Gutiérrez 2023: 87).",
    "AI can become a player in this space, \"a 'human-like' critical agent in the conversation where the technology invites a range of voices, perspectives, ideas, and texts into students' sense-making\" (Gutierrez 2024, unpublished research proposal)."
